This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with the problem of training neural machine translation systems. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes practical solutions to handle the challenges of large-scale pretraining. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves the use of deep learning techniques for natural language processing. The paper also mentions the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for image captioning, which could place it under cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper mentions the use of parallel computing to speed up training, which could place it under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
